name: r-svglite
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "2.1.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-svglite
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/svglite_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/svglite/svglite_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: ad40f590c7e80ae83001a3826b6e8394ba733446ed51fd55faeda974ab839c9b

build:
  number: 0
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-bh                       # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-rcpp                     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-gdtools                  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-bh
    - r-rcpp
    - r-gdtools >=0.1.6
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    # BH is the header-only part of Boost and thus a compile-time requirement only
    # - r-bh
    - r-rcpp
    - r-gdtools >=0.1.6

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('svglite')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('svglite')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/r-lib/svglite
  license: GPL-2.0-or-later
  summary: A graphics device for R that produces 'Scalable Vector Graphics'. 'svglite' is a fork of the older 'RSvgDevice' package.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - sachalau

# Package: svglite
# Version: 1.2.2
# Title: An 'SVG' Graphics Device
# Description: A graphics device for R that produces 'Scalable Vector Graphics'. 'svglite' is a fork of the older 'RSvgDevice' package.
